The paper deals with a communication problem involving coding and information theory, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The problem involves a network of users, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category. The problem is decentralized, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category. The paper also involves coding techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SI (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper deals with a specific variant of the Index Coding problem, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category.
